      "content": "You'd see the usual collection of broken things: men with eyes like chipped flint, leaning against peeling dumpsters, their faces etched with the permanent exhaustion of a life lived on the razor's edge. There are the slick, sharp-suited types, always watching, their smiles too wide and their hands too still. Then there are the others—the shadows themselves, draped in stained coats, moving with a slow, deliberate menace that promises trouble before you even see their faces. They aren't just people; they are pieces of the neighborhood's rot, waiting for the right moment to move.",
